  FAMOUS PEOPLE
============================================================

Name:          Nikola Tesla
Lived:         1856 - 1943
Nationality:   Serbian-American
Field:         Engineering
Known For:     AC electricity, induction motor
Contribution:  Alternating current power systems; Tesla coil; radio foundation
Quote:         "The present is theirs; the future is mine."

Name:          Alan Turing
Lived:         1912 - 1954
Nationality:   English
Field:         Computing
Known For:     Turing machine, codebreaking
Contribution:  Father of computer science; broke Enigma; Turing test for AI
Quote:         "We can only see a short distance ahead, but we can see plenty there that needs to be done."

Name:          Florence Nightingale
Lived:         1820 - 1910
Nationality:   English
Field:         Medicine
Known For:     Modern nursing
Contribution:  Founded modern nursing; used statistics; reduced Crimean War mortality 40% to 2%
Quote:         "I attribute my success to this: I never gave or took any excuse."

============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Categorical Imperative
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Act only on principles you could will to be universal laws
Philosopher:  Immanuel Kant
Example:      Don't lie; if universal lying existed, language would break down

Concept:      Empiricism
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   All knowledge comes from sensory experience; mind is blank slate
Philosopher:  Locke/Hume
Example:      We know fire burns because we felt it, not through pure reason

Concept:      Stoicism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Focus only on what is in your control; accept all else with equanimity
Philosopher:  Marcus Aurelius/Epictetus
Example:      Illness is not in your control; your response to it is

